      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(doctor): skip parent-level empty-group-allowlist warning when every account has groupAllowFrom",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nThe empty-allowlist scanner treated the top-level channel record as a standalone account. When the top-level had an empty `groupAllowFrom` (or fell back to the DM `allowFrom`), doctor warned that **all group messages would be silently dropped** — even when every configured account supplied its own non-empty `groupAllowFrom` and the parent scope was a pure fallback never read at runtime.\n\n## Fix\n\n- Scan accounts before checking the parent scope\n- Suppress the parent-level group-allowlist-empty warning when **every** enabled account already carries its own populated `groupAllowFrom`\n- DM-allowlist warnings, per-account warnings, and the parent warning when accounts are missing or incomplete are **unchanged**\n\n## Files changed\n- `src/commands/doctor/shared/empty-allowlist-scan.ts` — collect enabled accounts, compute `allAccountsHaveGroupAllowlist`, pass into `checkAccount`\n- `src/commands/doctor/shared/empty-allowlist-policy.ts` — honor new `allAccountsHaveGroupAllowlist` opt to skip parent-only group warning\n- `src/commands/doctor/shared/empty-allowlist-scan.test.ts` — 3 new test cases\n\n## Testing\n\n```\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/commands/doctor/shared/empty-allowlist-scan.test.ts\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/commands/doctor/shared/channel-doctor.test.ts\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/telegram/src/doctor.test.ts\n```\n\nAll 39 tests pass (6 new + 33 existing). No regressions.\n\nCloses #92684",
        "branch": "fix/92684-empty-allowlist-false-positive",
